From 8d102a9e5aa9be3f854af6fd58106e0edbbbad0f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
Date: Sun, 25 Jan 2026 13:10:47 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ASK: Add CMM integration for PPPoE relay hardware offload

Integrates pppoe-relay with NXP CMM (Connection Manager Module) daemon
for hardware-accelerated PPPoE relay forwarding. When relay sessions are
created or destroyed, the relay notifies CMM to install/remove fast path
entries.

Changes:
- Link pppoe-relay with libcmm
- Add CMM IPC calls on session create/destroy
- Add PID file management (/var/run/pppoerelay.pid)
- Clean SIGTERM handling (sends PADT to peers before exit)

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [NXP ASK extensions]

